<p><strong>Tripping Over the Lunch Lady and Other School Stories</strong></p>
<p><em>Question 1:</em> <strong>What is the main idea of the book "Tripping Over the Lunch Lady and Other School Stories"?</strong></p>
<p><em>Answer:</em> The book is a collection of humorous short stories about a young boy's experiences in elementary school, focusing on the misadventures and awkward moments that occur in everyday school life.</p>
<p><em>Question 2:</em> <strong>Who is the main character in the stories?</strong></p>
<p><em>Answer:</em> The main character is a young boy named Ethan, who narrates his experiences in a relatable and often humorous way.</p>
<p><em>Question 3:</em> <strong>What is the setting of the stories?</strong></p>
<p><em>Answer:</em> The stories are set in an elementary school, with various locations featured such as the cafeteria, the classroom, the playground, and the gymnasium.</p>
<p><em>Question 4:</em> <strong>What is a memorable moment from the book?</strong></p>
<p><em>Answer:</em> One memorable moment occurs when Ethan accidentally trips over the lunch lady, sending her tray of food flying into the air. Ethan's efforts to clean up the mess only lead to further chaos.</p>
<p><em>Question 5:</em> <strong>What is the overall tone of the book?</strong></p>
<p><em>Answer:</em> The book has a lighthearted and humorous tone, capturing the humorous and often embarrassing experiences that students encounter during their school days. The stories celebrate the joys and challenges of childhood and the bonds formed with friends and classmates.</p>